2025.statement_latex:
Birgit has ten candles. Each candle has a burning time of three hours. At one point, she lights one of those candles. From that moment on, she wants the ten candles to burn under the following conditions:

1. each subsequent candle is lighted only after a whole number of hours;

2. at least one candle should burn at all times;

3. no candle is blown out;

4. if in a period between two whole hours one particular candle or combination of candles burns, then it is not allowed that in the next period between two whole hours the same candle or combination of candles burns.

Under those conditions, what is the maximum number of hours until all 10 candles are burnt out?

A) 12 B) 15 C) 16 D) 17 E) 18

